{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# S3 — Gerrit project + LLM-Review label + submit requirement + submitWholeTopic\n\n## Why\nThis is the gate's integrity rule: a change is submittable ONLY when the deterministic\n`LLM-Review` vote is MAX and there are no unresolved comments. `copyCondition` avoids\nre-paying for an expensive LLM review on trivial rebases; `submitWholeTopic` lands whole\nreviewed features atomically. The integrity property is not just \"the label gates submit\"\nbut \"ONLY the bot can set the label\" — so a human cannot cast `LLM-Review` and trivially\nbypass the gate. Gerrit is pinned to **3.14.1** (set in d251's docker-compose), so every\npredicate/feature used here (`-has:unresolved`, `copyCondition`, submit requirements) is\nwell above its minimum version and was validated to parse against live 3.14.1.\n\n## What\n- Create the `rebar` project in Gerrit (NoteDb).\n- `LLM-Review` label in `refs/meta/config` (project.config): `function=NoBlock`; values\n  `-1..+1`; `copyCondition=changekind:TRIVIAL_REBASE OR changekind:NO_CODE_CHANGE`.\n  `function=NoBlock` is **required, not a free choice**: on Gerrit 3.14.1 a blocking label\n  function is rejected, so blocking MUST come from the submit requirement (below), and the\n  label function MUST be `NoBlock`. (Documented inline as a comment in `project.config`.)\n- Submit requirement (in project.config) `submittableIf = label:LLM-Review=MAX AND\n  -has:unresolved`. This is what actually blocks submit; the label is advisory on its own.\n  Both predicates were validated to parse (HTTP 200) on live Gerrit 3.14.1.\n- `change.submitWholeTopic=true` — set in the **server-level** `gerrit.config` under the\n  `[change]` section, NOT in `refs/meta/config`/`project.config` (it is a server-global\n  key and is silently ignored if placed in project.config). Written before Gerrit starts.\n- Access controls: grant the auto-generated `label-LLM-Review` vote permission to the\n  **Service Users** group; humans may push changes for review but cannot submit without the\n  label, and cannot themselves cast `LLM-Review`. The Service Users group is created/wired\n  in **S4** (see Scope) — S3 lands a config that references it and is end-to-end testable\n  in S3 by an **admin** casting the vote manually (the bot-only restriction is exercised in\n  S4 once the bot account exists).\n\n## Scope\nIn: project + `LLM-Review` label + submit requirement + server-level topic config + the\nlabel ACL grant (to the Service Users group reference). The ACL grant is authored here but\nits end-to-end \"only the bot votes\" proof is completed in S4 (the bot account does not yet\nexist in S3); in S3 the vote is exercised by an admin to prove the submit-requirement\nmechanics. Out: the bot account itself + event/vote wiring (S4); replication (S5); GitHub\nlockdown (S6). Gerrit version is fixed upstream by d251 (3.14.1) — S3 does not choose or\ndeploy a version, it only configures the project on that instance.\n\n## Files\n- `infra/gerrit/project.config` (pushed to `refs/meta/config`): label, submit requirement,\n  copyCondition, ACL grant.\n- `infra/gerrit/gerrit.config` (server-level config, mounted before Gerrit starts):\n  `[change]\\n  submitWholeTopic = true`. (Impl note: this is the same gerrit.config the\n  d251 docker-compose mounts; S3 adds/owns the `[change]` section. If d251 already provides\n  a gerrit.config, S3 patches the `[change]` section into it rather than creating a new one.)\n- `infra/gerrit/setup-project.sh`: provisions the project + pushes `refs/meta/config`.\n  Impl notes for the executor (not separate ACs): (a) **idempotent** — re-running must not\n  duplicate label/submit-req stanzas (push a fully-declarative project.config via\n  `git push HEAD:refs/meta/config`, and guard project creation with a check-before-create),\n  so CI re-provisioning / DR re-runs are safe; (b) **auth** — the script needs Gerrit admin\n  credentials to push `refs/meta/config` (admin HTTP password or SSH key); document the\n  credential source (env var / SSM) at the top of the script and fail-fast with a clear\n  message if absent; (c) **dry-run** — support a `--dry-run`/diff mode that prints the\n  intended config change before mutating the live instance.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A change can be pushed for review to the `rebar` project; submit is BLOCKED until\n      `LLM-Review=+1` (MAX) AND there are no unresolved comments — verified by an admin\n      casting the vote (the bot-only path is proven in S4). Both `label:LLM-Review=MAX` and\n      `-has:unresolved` predicates parse and enforce on Gerrit 3.14.1.\n- [ ] The `label-LLM-Review` vote permission is granted **exclusively** to the Service\n      Users group: an account NOT in that group (a regular developer) cannot cast the\n      `LLM-Review` vote (push with `%l=LLM-Review+1` is rejected / the vote is not applied),\n      while a Service-Users member can. (Bot membership is wired in S4; in S3 verify the\n      grant targets only the Service Users group, e.g. an admin-or-service vote succeeds and\n      a plain developer vote is refused.)\n- [ ] `copyCondition` carries the `LLM-Review` vote across a trivial rebase / no-code-change\n      patchset (verified by amending with no diff change on Gerrit 3.14.1).\n- [ ] `change.submitWholeTopic=true` is set in the server-level `gerrit.config` `[change]`\n      section (NOT in project.config), AND the behavior is demonstrated: two changes pushed\n      under the same topic submit atomically together, and neither can be submitted\n      independently while its topic partner is open.\n- [ ] The submit requirement is the SINGLE code-review vote in v1 (no separate human\n      Code-Review and no CI Verified vote yet — those are follow-on epic 1fa8). This\n      single-LLM-gate stance is deliberate and temporary; record it briefly (one ADR/note,\n      e.g. `docs/adr/` or a comment in `project.config`) so the rationale and the planned\n      evolution (1fa8 adds human Code-Review + CI Verified) are captured."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782689168704482001,"uuid":"d358556d-7f77-47db-ab9c-decabfaddaea"}